'''Jovo Lukić''' ({{Lang-sr-Cyrl|Јово Лукић}}, {{IPA|sr|jôːʋo lǔkitɕ}}; born 28 November 1998) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Liga I]] club [[FC Universitatea Cluj|Universitatea Cluj]]. Born in Serbia, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Lukić started his professional career at [[FK Sloga Doboj|Sloga Doboj]], before joining [[FK Krupa|Krupa]] in 2018. In 2019, he was loaned to [[NK Zvijezda Gradačac|Zvijezda Gradačac]]. The following year, he signed with [[FK Borac Banja Luka|Borac Banja Luka]].

A former youth international for [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]], Lukić made his senior international debut in 2021.

==Early life==
Jovo and his family, who are ethnic [[Serbs of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Serbs]],<ref>{{cite news|author=<!-- not stated -->|url=https://sport.srpskainfo.com/fudbal/jovo-lukic-dijeli-prvo-mjesto-liste-strijelaca-i-ceka-poziv-zmajeva/|title='Ja sam Srbin iz Bosne, ne krijem to' Hoće li Jovo Lukić konačno biti u planovima Sergeja Barbareza|website=sport.srpskainfo.com|date=16 December 2025|accessdate=1 April 2026|language=serbian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260401193358/https://sport.srpskainfo.com/fudbal/jovo-lukic-dijeli-prvo-mjesto-liste-strijelaca-i-ceka-poziv-zmajeva/|archive-date=1 April 2026}}</ref> hail from [[Modriča]], Bosnia and Herzegovina, where they live. However, he was born in [[Šabac]], [[Serbia and Montenegro|FR Yugoslavia]] (present-day Serbia),<ref name="n1info.ba-Lukić-baraž">{{cite web |title=Jovo Lukić pred mečeve baraža otkrio kako je komšiji zapalio automobi, pa poručio: Čast mi je biti pozvan u reprezentaciju |url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/jovo-lukic-pred-meceve-baraza-otkrio-kako-je-komsiji-zapalio-automobi-pa-porucio-cast-mi-je-biti-pozvan-u-reprezentaciju/ |website=N1 info |access-date=17 March 2026 |language=bs-BA |date=17 March 2026}}</ref><ref name="Rep.ba-Čast">{{cite web |title=VIDEO/ Jovo Lukić: Čast je igrati za nacionalni tim, čak i da ne igram |url=https://reprezentacija.ba/504197-jovo-lukic-cast-je-igrati-za-nacionalni-tim-cak-i-da-ne-igram |website=Reprezentacija.ba |access-date=17 March 2026 |language=bs-BA |date=17 March 2026}}</ref> on 28 November 1998.

==Club career==
===Early career===
Lukić started playing football at [[FK Alfa Modriča|Modriča]], before joining youth setup of [[FK Sloga Doboj|Sloga Doboj]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://mondo.ba/sport/fudbal/a959925/jovo-lukic-u-odabranom-drustvu-sa-21-godinom-najbolji-strijelac-lige|title=Jovo Lukić u odabranom društvu, sa 21 godinom najbolji strijelac lige|website=mondo.ba|date=22 May 2020|accessdate=24 May 2020|language=Bosnian}}</ref> He made his professional debut against [[FK Sutjeska Foča|Sutjeska Foča]] on 6 August 2016 at the age of 17.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/sutjeska-sigurna-u-doboju/202710|title=Sutjeska sigurna u Doboju|website=sportsport.ba|date=6 August 2016|accessdate=9 August 2016|language=Bosnian}}</ref> On 19 November, he scored his first professional goal in a triumph over [[FK Kozara Gradiška|Kozara Gradiška]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/sloga-odnijela-tri-boda-iz-gradiske/214581|title=Sloga odnijela tri boda iz Gradiške|website=sportsport.ba|date=19 November 2016|accessdate=19 November 2016|language=Bosnian}}</ref> Lukić scored his first career [[Hat-trick#Association football|hat-trick]] against [[FK Borac Šamac|Borac Šamac]] on 10 June 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/pobjede-slavije-i-sloge-remi-slobode-mg-i-sutjeske/240636|title=Pobjede Slavije i Sloge, remi Slobode MG i Sutjeske|website=sportsport.ba|date=10 June 2017|accessdate=11 June 2017|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

In February 2018, he moved to [[FK Krupa|Krupa]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/jovo-lukic-novi-igrac-krupe/384531|title=Jovo Lukić novi igrač Krupe|website=sportsport.ba|date=6 February 2018|accessdate=6 February 2018|language=Bosnian}}</ref> In February 2019, he was loaned to [[NK Zvijezda Gradačac|Zvijezda Gradačac]] until the end of season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/jovo-lukic-novo-pojacanje-gradacacke-zvijezda/307270|title=Jovo Lukić novo pojačanje gradačačke Zvijezde|website=sportsport.ba|date=20 February 2019|accessdate=21 February 2019|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

On 20 June 2020, Lukić signed with [[FK Borac Banja Luka|Borac Banja Luka]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/vijest/jovo-lukic-tri-godine-u-borcu/87609|title=Jovo Lukić tri godine u Borcu|website=faktor.ba|date=20 June 2020|accessdate=22 June 2020|language=Bosnian}}</ref> He debuted for Borac in a league game against [[FK Mladost Doboj Kakanj|Mladost Doboj Kakanj]] on 1 August 2020.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/fk-borac-deklasirao-fk-mladost/370413|title=FK Borac deklasirao FK Mladost|website=sportsport.ba|date=1 August 2020|accessdate=1 August 2020|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

On 9 September 2024, Lukić signed with [[CS Universitatea Craiova|Universitatea Craiova]],<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Universitatea Craiova|url=https://www.ucv1948.ro/Bine-ai-venit-la-Stiinta-Jovo-Lukic|title=Bine ai venit la Știința, Jovo Lukic!|trans-title=Welcome to Science, Jovo Lukic!|date=9 September 2024|access-date=10 September 2024|language=ro}}</ref> and in 2025 moved to [[FC Universitatea Cluj|Universitatea Cluj]], both clubs of [[Liga I|Romanian Liga I]].<ref name="gsp.ro-Cei 3 jucători-Lukic">{{cite web |last1=Manolache |first1=Liviu |date=24 December 2025 |title=Cei 3 jucători-revelație din acest acest sezon de Superliga » Doi au retrogradat în vară, altul a fost dat afară de fosta echipă |url=https://www.gsp.ro/fotbal/liga-1/uta-alin-roman-u-cluj-jovo-lukic-botosani-mailat-883639.html |access-date=25 December 2025 |website=www.gsp.ro |language=ro}}</ref>

==International career==
Lukić was a member of [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national under-21 football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina under-21 team]] under coach [[Vinko Marinović]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/reprezentacija/objavljen-spisak-mlade-reprezentacije-bih-za-meceve-sa-velsom-i-moldavijom/1849505|title=Objavljen spisak mlade reprezentacije BiH za mečeve sa Velsom i Moldavijom|website=fokus.ba|date=20 August 2020|accessdate=20 August 2020|language=Bosnian}}</ref> and earned his first senior cap for [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] on 19 December 2021 in a friendly 1–0 defeat to the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]].

On 9 March 2026, Lukić earned a recall to the senior national team under coach [[Sergej Barbarez]] for the play-off matches in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA second round|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]], first of which was an away win against [[Wales national football team|Wales]] on 26 March, and then win against [[Italy national football team|Italy]] in [[Zenica]] 5 days later.<ref name="reprezentacija.ba-ko-je-novi">{{cite web |title=Ko je novi Barbarezov napadač? Najbolji je strijelac u Rumuniji, a već je jednom igrao za Zmajeve |url=https://reprezentacija.ba/503414-ko-je-novi-barbarezov-napadac-najbolji-je-strijelac-u-rumuniji-a-vec-je-jednom-igrao-za-zmajeve |website=Reprezentacija.ba |access-date=10 March 2026 |language=bs-BA |date=9 Mar 2026}}</ref><ref name="reprezentacija.ba-barbarez-objavio-celik-i-lukic">{{cite web |title=Barbarez objavio spisak, pa poručio: Čelik i Lukić su to zaslužili |url=https://reprezentacija.ba/503413-barbarez-objavio-spisak-pa-porucio-celik-i-lukic-su-to-zasluzili |website=Reprezentacija.ba |access-date=10 March 2026 |language=bs-BA |date=9 Mar 2026}}</ref> However, Jovo did not enter official squad list for these matches due to arm injury.<ref name="meridiansport.ba-Poznato">{{cite web |title=Poznato zašto je Jovo Lukić oba meča baraža bio na tribinama |url=https://meridiansport.ba/featured/zasto-je-jovo-lukic-bio-na-tribinama/ |website=meridiansport.ba |access-date=13 April 2026 |date=7 April 2026}}</ref> On May 29th, Jovo started a friendly match against [[North Macedonia national football team|Macedonia]] at [[Koševo City Stadium|Koševo]], which was played as a preparation for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, and played the entire first half.<ref name="Rep.ba-2026-Jovo-izjava">{{cite web |title=VIDEO/ Jovo Lukić: Nema boljeg osjećaja nego igrati za svoju državu |url=https://reprezentacija.ba/514032-jovo-lukic-nema-boljeg-osjecaja-nego-igrati-za-svoju-drzavu |website=Reprezentacija.ba |access-date=30 May 2026 |language=bs-BA |date=29 May 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Lukić's father [[Mitar Lukić|Mitar]] was also a professional footballer.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sport1.oslobodjenje.ba/s1/fudbal/premijer-liga-bih/fudbaler-borca-na-meti-inostranog-kluba-za-koji-je-igrao-i-njegov-otac-da-li-ce-se-historija-ponoviti-616557|title=Fudbaler Borca na meti inostranog kluba za koji je igrao i njegov otac: Da li će se historija ponoviti?|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=30 December 2020|accessdate=30 December 2020|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

Lukić married his long-time girlfriend Zorana. Together they have a son.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/jovo-lukic-postao-otac-u-23-godini/397416|title=Jovo Lukić postao otac u 23. godini|website=sportsport.ba|date=24 April 2021|accessdate=25 April 2021|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

